description: an American singer and songwriter. He is known as the "King of Pop" and popularized the dance move "Moonwalk" which has become his trademark. His 1982 album Thriller is the world's best-selling album, with sales exceeding 104 million copies worldwide. He began his singing career at the age of five as a member of the Jackson family vocal group (later the Jackson 5) before releasing his first solo album Got to Be There in 1971. As the seventh child of the Jackson family, he debuted in professional music at the age of 11. years as a member of the Jackson 5.
